This is the stop closest to Carver High School. Students often use this stop. Carver Market / Community Grounds has placed a bench and trash can here. However, the trash piles up very quickly. We have asked for a shelter here and have been approved. But don't know when it will go in.

The bus is always lat by 30 minutes and it only comes once every hour on a regular day. The bus stop has no kind of formal waiting area. The “boarding area” is the turning lane in the middle of the street!!! There is a poison ivy plant growing on the fence of the grass area near the bus stop sign. When it’s raining outside the entire area is nothing but mud and trash every where. And when it rains cars splash water on you. I hate this stop!!!
